<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8130431>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Discias forsskali sp. nov., Saudi Arabian side of Gulf of Aqaba, northern Red Sea, holotype, ovigerous female (pocl 2.7 mm, cl 3.8 mm), FLMNH UF 68639: A, habitus, right lateral (fourth pereiopod missing, drawn based on its left side homolog); B, frontal region, lateral; C, rostral region and eyes, dorsal; D, detail of rostrum, dorsal; E, left antenna, ventral; F, left mandible, mesial; G, same, lateral; H, same, detail of molar process; I, left maxillule, lateral; J, left maxilla, lateral; K, left first maxilliped, lateral; L, left second maxilliped, lateral; M, left third maxilliped, lateral; N, same, ultimate article, dorsomesial." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8130431/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8130433>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Discias forsskali sp. nov., Saudi Arabian side of Gulf of Aqaba, northern Red Sea, holotype, ovigerous female (pocl 2.7 mm, cl 3.8 mm), FLMNH UF 68639:A, left first pereiopod, lateral; B, same, mesial; C, same, chela, ventral; D, same, distal portion of chela, dorsal; E, right first pereiopod, distal portion of chela, ventral; F, left second pereiopod, lateral; G, same, carpus and chela, ventral (mesial); H, same, carpus and chela, dorsal (lateral); I, left third pereiopod, lateral; J, same, distal portion of carpus, propodus and dactylus, lateral; K, left fourth pereiopod, lateral; L, same, distal portion of carpus, propodus and dactylus, lateral; M, left fifth pereiopod, lateral; N, same, distal portion of carpus, propodus and dactylus, lateral; O, telson and right uropod, dorsal; P, telson, distal margin." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8130433/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

